                        </button>
                    </h2>
                    <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFour"
                        data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>Track your expenses to be aware of where your money is going and to anticipate future
                                expenses.
                            </p>
                            <p>Keep a budget to avoid overspending and unnecessary stress.</p>
                            <p>If you are on a tight budget, consider your interests and ask US students and other
                                international students what local
                                activities you might enjoy.</p>
                            <p>If your budget allows, look for activities that you might enjoy outside of the region
                                where your university is located.
                                Ask well-traveled students for suggestions of enjoyable destinations.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFive">
                        <button class="accordion-button text-dark collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                            data-bs-target="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive">
                            <h2 style="font-size: 3.5vh">Be sure to purchase all materials needed for your classes
                                before the term begins</h2>
                        </button>
                    </h2>
                    <div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFive"
                        data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>
                                Examine course descriptions and syllabi carefully. Determine if you’ll need:
                            </p>
                            <p> text books; study materials; resources or tools recommended by the professor; required
                                software;
                                a backpack, notebooks, and writing utensils.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingSix">
                        <button class="accordion-button text-dark collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                            data-bs-target="#collapseSix" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseSix">
                            <h2 style="font-size: 3.5vh">Become familiar with your university</h2>
                        </button>
                    </h2>
                    <div id="collapseSix" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingSix"
                        data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>
                                It is a good idea to tour your campus as soon as possible. This will help you become
                                familiar with the new environment
                                and allow you to feel more comfortable as you make your way to your classes in the first
                                few weeks of school.
                            </p>
                            <p>You should be familiar with your university’s grading policies and the grading systems of
                                each of your courses. This
                                will help you set appropriate academic goals and will prevent surprises caused by not
                                understanding university or
                                professor expectations.
                            </p>
                            <p>Finally, you should be aware if courses at your university are often impacted. Are there
                                more students who wish to
                                enroll in a course than there are available spaces? Whether this is the case or not, it
                                is always a good idea to enroll
                                in your courses as soon as possible to avoid disappointment, or worse, being delayed in
                                taking courses needed to
                                complete your academic program.
                            </p>
                            <p>Don’t be afraid to ask questions and accept help from others as you seek answers to these
                                questions and any other
                                questions that may arise during your academic journey.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-item">
