                    <div id="collapseSeven" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingSeven"
                        data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <p>
                                Checking your university email and any professional emails you might have will help you
                                stay up-to-date on important
                                opportunities, deadlines, and activities happening around campus.
                            </p>
                            <p>Visit the school website regularly to stay updated on campus resources and activities.
                                Attend virtual information sessions. These information sessions can be a way of
                                networking and making connections. You
                                also obtain information that may be helpful for you during your time at the school and
                                beyond.
                            </p>
                            <p>Stay connected to the international student office and your advisors. Your international
                                student office advisors may
                                send you information via email to let you know about important events, deadlines, and
                                recommendations. Be sure to review
                                your email regularly to ensure that you stay up-to-date on this information.
                            </p>
                        </div>
